OL,6,FThat's almost nine times the level
OL,7,Fseen in the whole of 2023.
OL,9,FSpike survived but the respiratory
OL,10,Finfection led to life-changing
OL,11,Fconsequences. He's brain damaged, has
OL,12,Fdelayed speech and cerebral palsy.
OL,14,FAt 16, he just enjoyed his summer prom
OL,15,Fbut he won't be able to experience the
OL,16,Fsame independence as other teenagers.
OL,18,FSusan said: "He can't even do simple
OL,19,Fthings like going out on his own.
OL,20,FWhooping cough robbed me of my son.
