OL,6,F"I mourn for that child that I lost. I
OL,7,Fhave a different child, but the boy
OL,8,Fthat I lost, I still mourn for that
OL,9,Fchild. It never goes.
OL,11,F"He's on daily medication because he
OL,12,Fdeveloped epilepsy as a result of the
OL,13,Fbrain injury. He takes melatonin to
OL,14,Fmake him go to sleep. This is all a
OL,15,Fresult of the whooping cough."
OL,17,FA jab for expectant mothers was made
OL,18,Favailable in 2012, five years too late
OL,19,Ffor Susan.
